      About this item

      • Forever Power, Solar Style: The power never stops with this security system. Just 3 hours* of direct sunlight each day is enough to continuously power solar camera security outdoors, so you never have to worry about changing the battery. And when night rolls up or a rain shower strikes, the built-in battery keeps the juice flowing
      • Active Deterrence: The ultra-bright 600 Lumens spotlight switches on as soon as motion is detected, shining a light on any unwanted guests, while the color night vision picks out details in the darkness up to 8 meters away
      • No Hidden Costs: The wireless security cameras are a one-time purchase. There are no monthly fees or hidden costs. Everything is done on-device for complete security and transparency
      • Minimize False Notifications - Always be notified when there is a person on your property with Person Detection. Only receive notifications that are important to you on the Kittyhok app, even while youre away from home
      • Expandable 10CH NVR: NVR supports up to 10 cameras, You can add Battery Camera, 24/7 WiFi Security Camera, and PTZ Dome Security Camera, to meet your individual needs

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        • cavalierdog
          5.0 out of 5 stars Easy setup, really effortless to get running
          Reviewed in the United States on October 14, 2023
          Verified Purchase
          As background, I bought this and set it up two days before a week-long trip 2000 miles to Mom's house. So I only had precious little time to experiment hands-on and make everything right. I put the cameras up, in places that I thought would be OK, and it turns out that they were wide-angle enough such that it covered 100% of what I hoped for. And the movement and lighting settings are sophisticated, and poorly explained, but they work exactly as you might hope -- they are quite good.

          My biggest concern was that the mini solar panels would charge the cameras enough during the day so that they would work at night. Fortunately the battery state is included on the video display so you always know how it's going. Mine are always nearly full or all full. Their power management is surprisingly good. (I think the way it's working is to stay in a sleep mode until it sees movement, at which time it starts streaming video to the base unit, where you can watch it in real time or later.)

          I did spend a lot of time getting familiar with the system remotely during that week, and kept being pleasantly surprised by what I could do from my phone. It appears that a lot of thought and fine tuning has gone into this for usability and simplicity, while still being fully capable.

          One important thing to re-state, the video lives on your unit at home, and "cloud storage" is optional. This has the effect of (assume your base unit is on a UPS) if you lose internet and power, your 4-camera system is still 100% functional. And once the services come back up, you can review what happened while things were shut down.

          I did decide to move one of the cameras to a blind spot out back. This was three screws out, three screws in to the new location. All while powered up, and now I have a video of me using a screwdriver. (Of course, if someone steals or tampers with your camera, you will get a great video of who done it.)

          I've owned several Lorex systems considered the best in the business, all good, but ALL requiring an ethernet line to the hub. This Kittyhok system is truly wireless internet.
